<HEAD>Black Man Shot During On-Site Investigation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police say they shot and killed
a black man when he allegedly tried to set off a grenade while
accompanying officers on a field investigation.
   He was the fourth black man killed in the past two months during
a police on-site investigation. Two of the others died during
alleged escape attempts while handcuffed, according to police
reports.
   Police did not identify the 35-year-old man killed Monday at the
Khayelitsha black township near Cape Town. A statement from police
headquarters in Pretoria said he was linked to several slayings, but
did not say if he was charged.
   The statement said he was taken to Khayelitsha to show ``certain
sites. ... He took a hand grenade from a hole he had dug in the
ground and tried to pull the safety pin.
   ``A member of the police fatally wounded him, in a bid to prevent
him from pulling the pin,'' it said.
