<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--FastFreighter     01-24 0152</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Fast Freighter,0155</SECOND>
<HEAD>Japan Seeks to Develop High-Speed Ocean Freighter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Japan will launch a five-year project to develop a
freighter than can sail 2{ times faster than container vessels now
in operation, an official said Tuesday.
   Tasuku Hirahara of the Transport Ministry's Technology Division
said $4.3 million has been earmarked for the project. The budget
still is subject to approval by parliament.
   The vessel would have a speed of more than 58 mph, compared with
the average speed of 23 mph of current container vessels, Hirahara
said.
   The new vessel, about 330 feet long and capable of carrying more
than 1,000 tons, could travel to the United States in about three
days, or about half the time now needed for ocean crossings, he
added.
   The first of the new commercial liners, needing fewer than 10
crew members, would be operating before the end of this century,
Hirahara said.
</TEXT>
