<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Zimbabwe-Rhino     01-24 0182</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Zimbabwe-Rhino,0188</SECOND>
<HEAD>Wildlife Authorities Cancel Rhino Trip to Texas</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wildlife authorities Tuesday canceled a
plan to fly 10 rhinoceros to the United States.
   The rare black rhino were scheduled to be flown to the Fort
Worth, Texas, Zoo on Sunday, but mechanical problems delayed the
cargo plane, and Zimbabwe officials called off the operation, a
wildlife department spokesman said.
   The spokesman said the animals were in a weakened condition and
travel would be risky. No replacement aircraft was available Tuesday.
   The rhino were in crates for five days and were being released
under veterinary supervision, the spokesman added.
   The Zimbabwe news agency said the U.S. zoo will be asked to
renegotiate the acquisition of rhino for a captive breeding program
launched two years ago.
   The agency said Elvie Turner, the director of Forth Worth Zoo,
was in Harare to supervise the departure of the animals.
   ``We want to do what is best for the animals. If it has been felt
better not to keep them in crates anymore, it is fine,'' the agency
quoted Turner as saying.
</TEXT>
