<FIRST>r a AM-Bundy-Chronology     01-24 0461</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bundy-Chronology,0501</SECOND>
<HEAD>Theodore Bundy Chronology</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Bundy Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a chronology of Ted Bundy's Florida criminal history and
court appearances:
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1978:</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   Jan. 15 _ Margaret Bowman, 21, and Janet Lisa Levy, 20, strangled
at the Chi Omega sorority house at Florida State University,
Tallahassee.
   Feb. 9 _ Kimberly Leach, 12, reported missing from her junior
high school in Lake City.
   Feb. 15 _ Bundy arrested on charges of possession of stolen
property, Pensacola.
   July 21 _ Indicted for Leach kidnapping and murder.
   July 27 _ Indicted for Chi Omega murders.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1979:</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   July 24 _ Found guilty of first-degree murder in Chi Omega case.
   July 31 _ Sentenced to death by electrocution in Chi Omega
murders.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1980:</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   Feb. 7 _ Found guilty of first-degree murder in Leach case.
   Feb. 12 _ Sentenced to death for the Leach killing.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1984:</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   Sept. 24 _ Florida Supreme Court denies request for rehearing in
Chi Omega case.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1985:</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   July 11 _ Florida Supreme Court denies request for rehearing in
Leach case.
   Dec. 18 _ Clemency denied by Florida Board of Executive Clemency.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1986:</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   Feb. 5 _ Gov. Bob Graham signs death warrant in Chi Omega case.
   Feb. 13 _ U.S. Supreme Court denies request for stay in Chi Omega
case.
   Feb. 21 _ Florida Supreme Court denies request for stay in Chi
Omega case.
   Feb. 25 _ U.S. Supreme Court grants stay in Chi Omega case.
   May 22 _ Graham signs second death warrant in Chi Omega case.
   June 28 _ Trial judge denies stay in Chi Omega case.
   June 30 _ Florida Supreme Court denies stay in Chi Omega case.
   July 1 _ U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals grants stay in Chi Omega
case.
   Oct. 21 _ Graham signs death warrant in Leach case.
   Nov. 7 _ Trial judge denies stay in Leach case.
   Nov. 11 _ U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals denies stay in Leach case.
   Nov. 17 _ U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals grants stay in Leach case.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1987:</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   April 2 _ U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals orders hearing on Bundy's
competence to stand trial.
   Dec. 17 _ U.S. District Court denies incompetence claim.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1989:</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   Jan. 17 _ U.S. Supreme Court denies appeal in Leach case; Gov.
Bob Martinez signs second death warrant in Leach case.
   Jan. 19 _ Florida Circuit Court judge denies stay and appeal in
Leach case.
   Jan. 20 _ Florida Supreme Court denies appeal in Leach case.
   Jan. 21-22 _ U.S. District Court judge denies appeal in Leach
case; 11th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals refuses to heard appeal in
Leach case; Bundy confesses to killing 20 women in Washington,
Colorado, Utah and Idaho.
   Jan. 23 _ U.S. Supreme Court rejects Bundy's final appeal.
   Jan. 24 _ Bundy executed in Florida's electric chair.
</TEXT>
