<HEAD>Larger Production and Higher Prices Reported by Agency</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Catfish farmers ended 1988 with larger
production and higher prices than they did the year before, the
Agriculture Department said Tuesday.
   December output rose 10 percent from a year earlier to 22.6
million pounds of live weight, and prices averaged 78 cents per
pound, up 14 cents, the department's Agricultural Statistics Board
said.
   In all of last year, farm-grown catfish production was 295.1
million pounds, up 5 percent from 1987.
