<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 10am,0240</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prices were little changed in trendless early
trading on Wall Street today.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was up 4.29 to 2,222.68
as of 10 a.m. EST.
   Advancing issues were about even with decliners, as 420 stocks
rose, 438 declined and 572 were unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 19.92 million shares after the
first 30 minutes of trading.
   Peter VandenBerg, a market analyst with Shearson Lehman Hutton
Inc. said there was no clear trend early today, although prices rose
as Treasury bond prices moved higher.
   Hildegarde Zagorski, an analyst with Prudential-Bache Securities
Inc., said there was some continued profit-taking following Monday's
17-point drop in the Dow Jones industrial average.
   The most actively-traded issue on the NYSE was AT&amp;T, up ] to 29~.
   Pacific Telesis was unchanged at 31~ after announcing a
fourth-quarter earnings gain.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks was up
0.15 to 160.28. On the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index was down 0.38 to 317.65.
   On Monday the Dow Jones industrial average fell 16.97 points to
2,218.39.
   Declining issues outnumbered advances by about 5 to 3 on the
NYSE, with 550 up, 909 down and 504 unchanged.
   Big Board volume totaled 141.64 million shares, against 166.10
million in the previous session.
