<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prices moved higher on Wall Street today as
buyers took advantage of bargain stock prices following Monday's
decline.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was up 7.15 to 2,225.54
as of 11 a.m. EST.
   Advancing issues were slightly ahead of decliners, as 590 stocks
rose, 518 declined and 600 were unchanged on the New York Stock
Exchange.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 49.26 million shares after the
first 90 minutes of trading.
