<HEAD>Minkow Holding Bible Study in Jail While Waiting Fraud Sentence</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Barry Minkow, the youthful con artist
convicted of committing fraud through his ZZZZ Best rug shampooing
outfit, has been running a Bible study class for other federal
prisoners while awaiting sentencing, a prosecutor said.
   Jailers at the Metropolitan Detention Center refer to the group
of up to 10 inmates who meet nightly as ``Barry's boys,'' Assistant
U.S. Attorney Gordon Greenberg said after a court hearing Monday.
   ``He has the inmates listening to a sermon and Bible study,'' he
said.
   Minkow, 22, was convicted on 57 counts of fraud last month.
   He started his business in his parents' garage at age 15 and
became known through his TV advertisements. Though he was called a
business whiz kid and his company was traded on Wall Street,
investigators found it was an elaborate scheme and charged him with
multimillion-dollar securities fraud.
