<HEAD>Chrysler Increases Car and Truck Incentives</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HIGHLAND PARK, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chrysler Corp. on Tuesday increased
the number of car and truck models eligible for cash or low-interest
financing incentives.
   The No. 3 automaker offered cash rebates up to $2,000 or
financing as low as 7.7 percent on a wide range of 1988 and 1989
cars, trucks and vans. The offers continue indefinitely.
