<HEAD>Kohlberg Kravis Extends Deadline for Expiration of RJR Nabisco Offer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kohlberg Kravis Roberts Inc. said Tuesday it has
extended the deadline for expiration of its $24.53 billion tender
offer for RJR Nabisco Inc. until midnight Feb. 6.
   Kohlberg Kravis said in a statement the deadline was extended
because of the Federal Trade Commission's examination of the offer.
The FTC investigates proposed mergers to determine whether they
violate federal antitrust laws.
